Package: OptiSparseMET
Type: Package
Title: Sparse Multi-Environment Trial Design with Flexible Local Field Layout Construction
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      given = "Félicien",
      family = "Akohoue",
      email = "akohoue.f@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: Constructs sparse multi-environment trial designs by jointly
    addressing across-environment treatment allocation and within-environment
    field layout. Allocation supports random balanced and balanced incomplete
    strategies, optional common treatments for cross-environment connectivity,
    and optional structure-aware assignment guided by family labels or by
    groups derived from genomic or pedigree relationship matrices. Feasibility
    helpers (min_k_for_full_coverage(), suggest_safe_k(), warn_if_k_too_small())
    verify that per-environment capacity is sufficient to assign all treatments
    before allocation begins. Replication is determined by seed availability
    through assign_replication_by_seed(). Within-environment layouts are built
    via prep_famoptg() for repeated-check augmented, partially replicated, and
    RCBD-type designs, or via alpha_rc_stream() for fixed-grid alpha row-column
    designs. Optional mixed-model efficiency diagnostics are provided to
    evaluate designs prior to field deployment.
